    "Ivanič (1998) extends this notion, positing that writing serves as a socio-political medium for expressing identity.",
    "The academic realm, however, introduces complexities, notably around the contested concept of \"voice. \"",
    "Tardy (2012) acknowledges the broad spectrum of meanings attributed to \"voice, \" while Atkinson (2001) and Biber (2006) consider it a critical language aspect shaped by genre and community constraints in academic writing.",
    "While traditional perspectives on voice and authorship highlight the human dimension, the study at hand delves into a distinctive realm-assessing voice in a ChatGPT-generated text as an authorship marker.",
    "Conventional aspects of authorship will unavoidably change as AI becomes more prevalent in writing tasks, challenging the notion of voice as an extension of the human author."
